body.description: Inspired by classic mid-century design, the 47 inch Jen Wood Dining Table blends the natural beauty of solid wood with a compact, less-is-more silhouette. Crafted with round tapered legs and tabletop with rounded corners, this versatile piece refines a small dining area, nook or multipurpose room with understated elegance. It can comfortably seat 4 people and is made entirely from durable, solid wood with a finish that easily wipes clean. And best of all, assembling this beauty can be done in 2 simple steps. Plus, we even give you the tools to do it! If that weren’t enough, Jen is also backed with a 1-year worry-free warranty for peace of mind. With delivery and setup so seamless, even with limited space, having a magazine-ready spot to host your next gathering has never been this effortless.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This was an awesome buy - it arrived in perfect shape and was super easy to assemble (the little ratchet tool was chefs kiss)! I love the color, it’s super sturdy and very simple design - all for an affordable price. My house is 535 sq ft and this table was a great fit for my little dining area :)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 16, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Real wood table in excellent packaging for a very reasonable price!
reviews.reviewText: This table is amazing! It's thoughtfully packed; I assembled two different pieces of flat pack furniture today from two different companies, and this one was far superior. All the corners were protected by styrofoam inserts, all the styrofoam in the package was sealed in plastic (no styrofoam snow all over the place while I was unpacking and assembling!), and the hardware was blister packed on a cardboard card so nothing was roaming loose in the box. It came with the usual L-shaped hex tool, but Zinus also included their own branded hex tool with a nice handle that was much easier to work with. Eight bolts and you're done. The instructions have large, clear diagrams. The package also included an envelope with a thank you note and blank cards to send to friends/family. This company cares about its product AND its presentation!The table itself is lovely. I purchased the natural version, and in person it's a mellow honey color. The legs are solid wood with felt feet already attached, and the top is real wood all the way through. It is a pieced wood, not a solid top. I included a picture to show what it looks like because the joins are very visible, but not messy or unpleasant. The hardware was all heavy duty and included bolts and washers. It would be very easy to paint this table. It's also got a nice weight and it's sturdy enough that I dont anticipate any issues using it as a craft table.Some pictures show this table with two chairs on each of the long sides, but they'd have to be very narrow.This table was a great buy for around $100. I am so pleasantly surprised by the quality of the whole package at the price point...honestly, it put most of the other flat pack furniture I've bought or assembled to absolute shame. This is a great piece!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Pros: I love the style, color, and size of this table, and it was super easy to put together - all you do is attach the legs. It's very sturdy and doesn't wobble at all.Cons: I'm not crazy about the hairline crack running from one of the short edges toward the center of the table. It's not very noticeable, but it keeps me from giving the table a 5-star review. I noticed cracks mentioned in other reviews. Just be aware that it's an occasional issue and that it would be a huge hassle to return, so be prepared to get what you pay for, and if you're lucky, you won't have this problem.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Compact but sturdy dinning table
reviews.reviewText: The ZINUS dinning table is the perfect option for a small homes with limited dinning room space. Compact and sturdy, this table is attractive as well. Assembly is quick and easy, and the tools you need are provided, so all you need to do is attach the legs and your table is ready to use. Another plus is that, while the table is made of wood, the table is light enough that it can be moved easily to fit whatever you think it will fit best. The ZINUS table is versatile as well and can be used as a desk. Solid, attractive, easy to assemble, and versatile, this table will be a welcome addition to any small or mid-size home/room.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best and easiest assembly
reviews.reviewText: I am 84 so it was difficult to get the parts out of the box (about 30 minutes for my old hands) but it was super easy to assemble, especially with the ratchet like tool. My hands are not strong but, with the tool they supplied in addition to the "L" shaped tool, it was a breeze to put the legs on. It took me about 15 minutes. I was afraid once assembled I would not be able to set it upright but it was light enough to handle. I am totally happy with this table. It looks fine and seems quite sturdy. My thanks to the company for such careful packaging. Styrofoam encased in plastic kept cleanup to absolute minimum. Everything was included, nothing missing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Good size for small spaces but feels cheap and flimsy
reviews.reviewText: Table looks fine but its way too light weight. You don't want your kitchen table to be sliding if you bump into it and creaking when you rest your arms down. I had this table for a couple of weeks and it gets dents and scratches extremely easily. Not worth the money IMO. Better to get something slightly more expensive but will last you a longer time.
